commits.message:
Refactor backend services and add HTTP client functionality

- Updated Docker Compose configuration to change image names and add environment variables for app1 and app2.
- Reduced memory limits for app1 and app2 to optimize resource usage.
- Replaced Nginx with HAProxy for load balancing between app1 and app2, including configuration for socket connections.
- Added new C source files for HTTP client functionality, including GET and POST methods with timeout handling.
- Updated lakefile to include the new HTTP client object file in the build process.
- Introduced shared memory settings and timeout definitions in new header files.
- Implemented a utility function for getting the current time in milliseconds.

pull_request.title: Fix fetch invoices type error
pull_request.body: Fixes "TypeError: Failed to fetch" by ensuring API routes run on Node.js runtime and removing a client-side Node.js import. The "Failed to fetch" error was caused by Next.js API routes, which utilize Prisma and JWT, implicitly attempting to run on the unsupported Edge runtime. Explicitly setting `export const runtime = "nodejs";` for these routes forces them to use the Node.js runtime, resolving the underlying crash. Additionally, an unused Node.js-specific `process` import was removed from a client-side component to prevent potential browser-side issues. ---

commits.message:
feat: Add sidebar toggle and GPS breadcrumbs

This commit introduces two significant user experience improvements to the main interface.

1.  **Collapsible Sidebar Toggle**: The activity bar buttons (`Guides`, `Map`) now also function as a toggle for the sidebar. Clicking the currently active icon will collapse the sidebar, and clicking any icon will expand it if it's collapsed. This provides more control over the screen real estate.
2.  **GPS Breadcrumbs**: The "Live GPS Mode" now includes a breadcrumb trail feature. As the user moves, a red path is drawn on the map, showing their traveled route. This trail is automatically cleared when GPS tracking is stopped.

- **`js/main.js`**: Logic updated for the sidebar toggle and to implement the breadcrumb trail.
- **`css/style.css`**: Styles updated to support the collapsible sidebar on all screen sizes.

- [#​2261](https://redirect.github.com/withastro/starlight/pull/2261) [`778b743`](https://redirect.github.com/withastro/starlight/commit/778b743cdb832551ed576c745728358d8bbf9d7a) Thanks [@​shubham-padia](https://redirect.github.com/shubham-padia)! - Adds support for using any of Starlight‚Äôs built-in icons in asides.

- [#​3272](https://redirect.github.com/withastro/starlight/pull/3272) [`e7fe267`](https://redirect.github.com/withastro/starlight/commit/e7fe26720b7527c39e3aab42ea9fd0468f92167c) Thanks [@​delucis](https://redirect.github.com/delucis)! - Adds a new `generateId` option to Starlight‚Äôs `docsLoader()`

  This enables overriding the default sluggifier used to convert content filenames to URLs.

- [#​3276](https://redirect.github.com/withastro/starlight/pull/3276) [`3917b20`](https://redirect.github.com/withastro/starlight/commit/3917b206da26522f73bbe0c1120de9acae5972c5) Thanks [@​delucis](https://redirect.github.com/delucis)! - Excludes banner content from search results

  Previously, content set in [`banner`](https://starlight.astro.build/reference/frontmatter/#banner) in page frontmatter was indexed by Starlight‚Äôs default search provider Pagefind. This could cause unexpected search results, especially for sites setting a common banner content on multiple pages. Starlight‚Äôs default `Banner` component is now excluded from search indexing.

  This change does not impact `Banner` overrides using custom components.

- [#​3266](https://redirect.github.com/withastro/starlight/pull/3266) [`1161af0`](https://redirect.github.com/withastro/starlight/commit/1161af0c2fe26485da6123f8fd7205c53b0e45e5) Thanks [@​HiDeoo](https://redirect.github.com/HiDeoo)! - Adds support for custom HTML attributes on autogenerated sidebar links using the [`autogenerate.attrs`](https://starlight.astro.build/guides/sidebar/#custom-html-attributes-for-autogenerated-links) option.

- [#​3274](https://redirect.github.com/withastro/starlight/pull/3274) [`80ccff7`](https://redirect.github.com/withastro/starlight/commit/80ccff7c542794e04a4d2abb17227a076fa57c5d) Thanks [@​HiDeoo](https://redirect.github.com/HiDeoo)! - Fixes an issue where some Starlight remark and rehype plugins were transforming Markdown and MDX content in non-Starlight pages.

  ‚ö†Ô∏è **BREAKING CHANGE:**

  Previously, some of Starlight‚Äôs remark and rehype plugins, most notably the plugin transforming Starlight's custom Markdown syntax for [rendering asides](https://starlight.astro.build/guides/authoring-content/#asides), were applied to all Markdown and MDX content. This included content from [individual Markdown pages](https://docs.astro.build/en/guides/markdown-content/#individual-markdown-pages) and content from [content collections](https://docs.astro.build/en/guides/content-collections/) other than the `docs` collection used by Starlight.

  This change restricts the application of Starlight‚Äôs remark and rehype plugins to only Markdown and MDX content loaded using Starlight's [`docsLoader()`](https://starlight.astro.build/reference/configuration/#docsloader). If you were relying on this behavior, please let us know about your use case in the dedicated `#starlight` channel in the [Astro Discord](https://astro.build/chat/) or by [opening an issue](https://redirect.github.com/withastro/starlight/issues/new?template=---01-bug-report.yml).

- [#​3266](https://redirect.github.com/withastro/starlight/pull/3266) [`1161af0`](https://redirect.github.com/withastro/starlight/commit/1161af0c2fe26485da6123f8fd7205c53b0e45e5) Thanks [@​HiDeoo](https://redirect.github.com/HiDeoo)! - Ensures invalid sidebar group configurations using the `attrs` option are properly reported as a type error.

  Previously, invalid sidebar group configurations using the `attrs` option were not reported as a type error but only surfaced at runtime. This change is only a type-level change and does not affect the runtime behavior of Starlight which does not support the `attrs` option for sidebar groups.

commits.message:
[FIX] account: exchange with same foreign currency not in partial

After https://github.com/odoo/odoo/pull/204746, in some situations we will
default the amount of the partial on residual of debit aml even if this one is
larger than the credit aml amount.
This lead to multiple exchange moves creation that are not properly linked to
the reconciliation chain.

Steps to reproduce:
1/ Setup foreign currency with rate 0.648587 (ex 0.648587 USD = 1 AUD for AUD
company)
2/ Create invoice with lines
36 USD (55.51 AUD)
-7.2 USD (-11.1 AUD)
=> Receivable will be 28.8 USD (44.41 AUD)
3/ Register a payment of 28.8 USD (44.4 AUD)
=> Two exchange moves will be created with 0.01 in credit, none of them is in a
partial with the invoice or payment line

This PR makes sure that we take the smallest amount of residual if both credit
and debit are considered as fully matched.

X-original-commit: a456d9c7cbdf17edb5db2c73306b62150e46a7a7
Signed-off-by: Laurent Smet (las) <las@odoo.com>

[IMP] dun_and_bradstreet: send `industry_code` instead of `industry_id`

Ticket #4992568 highlighted a weird way of sending the industry from
IAP to the Odoo client. Before this commit, we were sending the IAP psql id
of the industry to the client. There, it would be use as is. It works because
these industries haven't been changed in years and they're created in the same
order.
However the ticket highlighted the fact that a user can edit/delete/create its
own industries, therefore some ids that exist on IAP might not exist on the client's
Odoo instance. This resulted in a traceback on the client's side

With this commit, we now send the industry code (the ISIC: International Standard
Industrial Classification) instead to the client. There it can correctly be mapped
if it exists on the client's DB (e.g. not deleted)

[FIX] bus: race condition and correct error in waitForChannels

This change addresses two issues in the `waitForChannels` test utility:
- Fixes a race condition. The `failTimeout` variable was sometimes accessed
before its `setTimeout` declaration had been executed. This happens when a fast
bus event triggers the `onWebsocketEvent` handler, resulting in a reference
error. The variable is now declared at the beginning of the function, making it
available before any access (fixes runbot-223252).
- Corrects error in def.reject. `message` only takes one param, and a string
does not have a join method.

[FIX] calendar: show meetings with no organizer in grouped view

__Issue__
In the calendar list view, meetings with no organizer and default
privacy (`privacy=False`) are excluded when grouping by Responsible and
Created On.

__Steps to Reproduce__
1. Create a meeting with:
   - `privacy` set to default,
   - no `organizer`
2. Go to Calendar > List view.
3. Group by Responsible, then by Created On.

‚Üí The meeting is missing from the view.

__Fix__
Adjust the domain to include meetings where:
- `privacy=False`, and
- either `user_id` is unset or their settings are in the public allowed
list.

pull_request.title: Add filtering options for hoerbuecher episodes table
pull_request.body:
This pull request adds advanced filtering capabilities to the audiobook episodes list, improves the `AudiobookEpisode` model with new accessors for episode type, roles filled, and release year, and refactors date parsing logic for better maintainability. It also introduces tests to ensure correct behavior of the new model accessors.

### Filtering and UI improvements

* Added filter controls to `hoerbuecher/index.blade.php` for status, type, year, and roles filled, allowing users to narrow down episodes in the UI.
* Implemented client-side filtering logic in `hoerbuecher.js` to show/hide episode rows based on selected filter criteria.
* Updated episode table rows to include new data attributes (`data-status`, `data-type`, `data-roles-filled`, `data-year`) for use by the filter logic.

### Model enhancements

* Added new accessors and methods to `AudiobookEpisode.php`: `all_roles_filled`, `isSpecialEdition`, `episode_type`, `planned_release_date_parsed`, and `release_year`, centralizing logic for episode classification and release date parsing.
* Refactored date parsing from controller to model, simplifying the controller and improving code reuse.

### Testing

* Added a feature test suite `AudiobookEpisodeModelTest.php` to verify the new model accessors for episode type, roles filled, and release year.

pull_request.title: Add filtering options for hoerbuecher episodes table
pull_request.body:
This pull request adds advanced filtering capabilities to the audiobook episodes list, improves the `AudiobookEpisode` model with new accessors for episode type, roles filled, and release year, and refactors date parsing logic for better maintainability. It also introduces tests to ensure correct behavior of the new model accessors.

### Filtering and UI improvements

* Added filter controls to `hoerbuecher/index.blade.php` for status, type, year, and roles filled, allowing users to narrow down episodes in the UI.
* Implemented client-side filtering logic in `hoerbuecher.js` to show/hide episode rows based on selected filter criteria.
* Updated episode table rows to include new data attributes (`data-status`, `data-type`, `data-roles-filled`, `data-year`) for use by the filter logic.

### Model enhancements

* Added new accessors and methods to `AudiobookEpisode.php`: `all_roles_filled`, `isSpecialEdition`, `episode_type`, `planned_release_date_parsed`, and `release_year`, centralizing logic for episode classification and release date parsing.
* Refactored date parsing from controller to model, simplifying the controller and improving code reuse.

### Testing

* Added a feature test suite `AudiobookEpisodeModelTest.php` to verify the new model accessors for episode type, roles filled, and release year.
